# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Environment Configuration — AI School
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Copy this file to .env and fill in the values.
# The app uses a Supabase-compatible backend (Lovable Cloud, 
# Supabase, or Memfire) and an OpenAI-compatible AI provider.

# ── Database / Backend ──────────────────────────────────────────
# Point these to your Supabase-compatible instance.
# For Memfire: use your Memfire project URL and anon key.
VITE_SUPABASE_URL="https://your-project.supabase.co"
VITE_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY="your-anon-key"
VITE_SUPABASE_PROJECT_ID="your-project-id"

# ── AI / LLM (Edge Function Secrets) ───────────────────────────
# These are configured as backend secrets, NOT in .env.
# Set them via your backend's secret management.
#
# DEEPSEEK_API_KEY       — API key for DeepSeek (current provider)
# AI_API_BASE_URL        — Base URL for the AI API (default: https://api.deepseek.com/v1)
#                          For Aliyun DashScope: https://dashscope.aliyuncs.com/compatible-mode/v1
# AI_MODEL               — Model identifier (default: deepseek-chat)
#                          For Aliyun: qwen-turbo, qwen-plus, qwen-max, etc.
# AI_API_KEY             — API key (same as DEEPSEEK_API_KEY currently, 
#                          will be the Aliyun API key after migration)
